parameters:
\N<Boss-kun>Oh? What is it, Boku-chan? Do you want
to go ahead...? I see, you must want to do some
'grass sliding,' huh?

\N<Boss-kun>What's the matter, don't you know?
Alright, I'll tell you, so go get a cardboard box.

\N<Boss-kun>If you go to the Aoki Store in the
shopping district, you can get one. Usually,
there's an old man at the store, but during summer
vacation, a somewhat intimidating onee-chan is
taking care of the shop.
\N<Boku>I see... Should I go and check it out?

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, Boku-chan. Did you bring the
cardboard box? In that case, let's have a
competition on the grass slope. If you can beat
me, I'll tell you a secret fishing spot.

\N<Boss-kun>Oh? Another competition on the grass
slope? Alright, let's do it!
Let's do it, let's do it!

\N<Boss-kun>You've got guts! In that case, let's
go all the way to the top of the ski resort.

\N<Boss-kun>Listen up. The rules are simple. We'll
slide down from here to the bottom and the one who
passes through the most checkpoints wins. The
checkpoints will be shining brightly to make them
noticeable.

\N<Boku>Checkpoints? So it's not just about being
fast?

\N<Boss-kun>There was a rule change a few years
ago because it was deemed dangerous to compete
solely based on speed.

\N<Boss-kun>Here's some advice for the end. Be
careful because you'll bounce if you hit any
bumps. Alright then, are you ready? Enough with
the chit-chat, let's begin!

\N<Boss-kun>What's wrong, did you get scared? Come
at me anytime.

\N<Boku>Yay! I won! So, where's the best fishing
spot?

\N<Boss-kun>Ugh, it's a secret, but I guess I have
no choice. It's a hidden waterfall where you can
catch big fish. It's hard to explain verbally...
Oh, do you have a map? Let me borrow it, I'll mark
the spot for you.

\N<Boss-kun>Alright then. I've hidden a rope at
this marked location. If you use this rope, you
can descend to the secret fishing spot at the
hidden waterfall. However, there's no path up
until here, so you'll have to swim across the
river to get there.

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, and also, I'm not entirely sure,
but there seems to be a legend that says 'Never
swim alone in the evening' at that waterfall over
there.

\N<Boss-kun>Well, I don't think anyone would
bother going swimming in a place like that in the
evening. But, don't forget that you can only catch
big fish in the evening.

\N<Boss-kun>Anyway, let's have another match on
the grass slope. I just happened to be in a bad
condition today, so I won't lose next time.

\N<Boss-kun>Damn it! I lost again! But, it's too
early to get cocky! Mika-chan is stronger than me,
after all.
\N<Boku>Yeah, I met her at school this morning.
\N<Boss-kun>Ah, it's my turn to water the plants.

\N<Mika-chan>Tetsu, Grandma said to come back home
soon because she's skipping cleaning the bath.

\N<Mika-chan>Geez, really. Oh, you're Boku-kun,
right? I was playing with Tetsu.

\N<Boss-kun>Y-Yeah, that's right! I lost in the
grass sliding, and if I keep losing like this to
the new recruits, it won't be good for my
reputation as the leader of the Hime-no-yama
Defense Squad!

\N<Boss-kun>Hey, Mika-ne, how about you have a
match with me? As the former leader of the Hime-
no-yama Defense Squad, protect the squad's
reputation for me!

\N<Mika-chan>No way. Why should I have to do
something like that? Besides, I'm going home right
away.

\N<Boss-kun>Haha, Mika-ne, are you scared? Well, I
am such a formidable opponent after all. Even for
you, Mika-ne, it might be impossible. Oh well,
can't be helped, right?

\N<Mika-chan>W-What? I never said I couldn't win,
you know?

\N<Boss-kun>You don't have to push yourself, Mika-
ne. Just gracefully admit defeat and let's go
home.

\N<Mika-chan>I told you, I haven't lost! Geez,
whatever! I'll just have a match with Boku-kun
then! Come on, let's go up already! Tetsu, go play
with the cardboard boxes!

\N<Boss-kun>Mika-ne is amazing, aren't they? They
really hate losing, don't they?

\N<Boss-kun>Mika-ne is my slightly older cousin.
They used to be the former leader of the Hime-no-
yama Defense Squad.
\N<Boku>Oh, really? I'd like to meet them.

\N<Boss-kun>Hmm, Mika-ne, it might be difficult to
meet them since they haven't been playing outside
lately.

\N<Boss-kun>Ah, but if it's the day for watering
duty, Mika-ne might be at school.

\N<Boku>I see... Maybe I should go and meet them
sometime...

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, it's a tie. We'll settle it
another time.

\N<Boss-kun>Heheh! I win! You're ten years too
early, Boku-chan!

\N<Boss-kun>Oh? Do you want to have a rematch with
Mika-ne?

\N<Boss-kun>That's what it means to be a man!
Alright, I'll go call Mika-ne!

\N<Mika-chan>Ouch... I guess it's no wonder I'm a
bit rusty... Ah... I'm covered in mud... I need to
clean up this dirt...

\N<Boku>Um... There's a big bath at my house
nearby, would you like to take a bath?

\N<Boss-kun>Boku-chan's house is a big pension
over there. I remember someone saying there's a
natural hot spring with a source bath...

\N<Mika-chan>Hmm, I see. Well, it's your fault
that it turned out like this, so I'll borrow your
bath.
\N<Boss-kun>Well then, I guess I'll go too.

\N<Mika-chan>Tetsu, you should hurry home and
clean the bath.

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, right... Well then, I'll go home!
See ya!

\N<Mika-chan>...Then, will you take me to your
house?

\N<Mika-chan>You, who managed to tie with me, have
quite an interesting side. Let's have a rematch
next time.

\N<Mika-chan>Your skills aren't bad, but you still
have a long way to go. If you have free time, I'll
give you a rematch.

\N<Mika-chan>You came here often, Boku! Now, let's
compete on the grass slide! Today, I'll show you
my true strength!
Let's skip it for today, okay?

\N<Mika-chan>Oh, is that so...? W-Well, I guess
there's no helping it.

\N<Mika-chan>Well, I lost...? Me...? Ugh, how
frustrating...!

\N<Mika-chan>Ugh, I get it! You want to do naughty
things, don't you! Geez! You pervert!

\N<Boku>Huh, w-wait...? Mika-chan was the one who
brought it up...

\N<Mika-chan>Ugh... W-was that so...? W-well, I
guess there's no helping it. A promise is a
promise, after all.

\N<Mika-chan>Um, well... in that case... my house
is not an option... so, I guess I'll be staying in
one of the guest rooms at the inn, right?

\N<Mika-chan>...Then, let's go to my room. We can
also use the bath there.

\N<Mika-chan>Who are you to tie with me when I'm
serious...?... For today, let's put the match on
hold...

\N<Mika-chan>Look! If I give it my all, this is
what happens! If you're frustrated, we can have a
rematch, you know? Well, even if we do it multiple
times, I think the result will be the same.
